profile_positions.description:
•	Responsible for setting out a clear vision and strategy, appropriate approach and priority actions for the EBRD in support of the SME Finance& Development Group strategic priorities related with private sector financing and promoting access to know how among the various stakeholders;
•	Present EBRD SME Finance & Development Group activities in public and lead meetings with donors and government in the country; Fundraising and managing relations with EU and international donors and various stakeholders, including with government and non governmental institutions. 
•	Manage relations with donor community including with government officials and international organisations and foreign embassies; 
•	The effective management of the donor funded EBRD SMEs Advisory in the country including managing of the TC budget of EUR 500,000 a year.
•	Managing and leading a team of 4 professionals toward helping privates sector companies with transferring industry knowledge and management skills, meeting standards required to complete both locally and within the EU, helping to innovate and to improve reporting and accounting structures, and to increase financial transparency and prepare them for future investments both through EBRD direct and indirect financing including trough WB EDIF and other financial intermediaries; 
•	Building and maintaining relations and cooperating with private companies, banks and financial intermediaries including with EBRD partners’ banks for supporting investment activities among the private sector including for implementation of Women in Business credit line, Competitiveness credit line, Energy Efficiency Facility (Webseff) and Risk Sharing facility. National Team Leader of the Western Balkan Women in Business Facility, sponsored by Sweden, Luxembourg and EBRD Shareholders Special Fund. 
•	Lead team: hiring, training, managing and developing 5-6 members of staff

•	Developing the strategy, objectives and the action plan and overseeing the implementation of the EU funded EBRD International Advisory Programme in Macedonia in cooperation with EBRD corporate banking department; 
•	Managing relations with EU and national stakeholders, including government officials and representatives of international organisations;
•	Business development, identifying and screening of  bankable mid cap companies from various sectors (market leaders) and developing international advisory projects (TC projects) in synergy with banking operation in areas including strategy, marketing, operations, quality management, energy efficiency, financial management. More than 40 international industry advisors engaged for clients companies and 4 Sector Development workshops organised for best management practises dissemination in Agribusiness, IT, Tourism and FMCG Industry.
•	Team Leader (January 2012- June 2012) of a complex EBRD IT project in London, resulted in successful implementation of a management information system (MIS) for EBRD International Advisory across 28 countries, providing significant benefits to the globally based business teams consisted of more than 100 people.

•	Promotion of  EBRD financial and non-financial instruments among the private sector and seeking investment projects from banks, industry associations, chambers and consultants;
•	Identification of bankable companies, performing business diagnostics and identification of their financing needs and business areas for improvement;
•	Scoping and tailoring advisory projects for SMEs clients, identification of suitable consultants for the assignments, monitoring project implementation and evaluating the impact. In total 466 advisory projects executed for 430 SMEs in support of access to finance.
•	Trainings and workshops organisation for dissemination of best management practices and capacity building of consultants; Instrumental for promoting the environmental consultancy and women entrepreneurship.
